1
00:00:45,337 --> 00:00:46,547
Chameleon!

2
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:50,259
Teo, run.

3
00:00:50,342 --> 00:00:51,635
- Run!
- Huh?

4
00:00:51,719 --> 00:00:52,636
Stop!

5
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:54,054
I have your friends!

6
00:01:01,854 --> 00:01:04,064
Wait, wait.

7
00:01:04,732 --> 00:01:05,566
Let's go.

8
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:51,278
I got you!

9
00:01:52,530 --> 00:01:53,697
Freeze!

10
00:02:00,246 --> 00:02:02,998
<i>Falling in love only feels good at first.</i>

11
00:02:03,082 --> 00:02:06,252
<i>It makes you happy</i>
<i>and see the beauty of things.</i>

12
00:02:07,670 --> 00:02:12,424
<i>You don't notice that</i>
<i>you're slowly drowning in it.</i>

13
00:02:13,008 --> 00:02:16,095
<i>Only then you'll see</i>
<i>what's wrong in your relationship.</i>

14
00:02:16,887 --> 00:02:19,849
<i>- Every ugly and painful truth.</i>

15
00:02:19,932 --> 00:02:20,975
Yana, turn yourself in!

16
00:02:24,645 --> 00:02:26,522
<i>And when you realize that,</i>

17
00:02:28,566 --> 00:02:29,775
<i>it's already too late.</i>

18
00:02:31,443 --> 00:02:32,987
<i>There's no getting out.</i>

19
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,865
<i>You can't get back up anymore.</i>

20
00:02:37,908 --> 00:02:39,159
<i>You're left with no choice.</i>

21
00:02:39,243 --> 00:02:40,494
Surrender to the cops.

22
00:02:43,247 --> 00:02:45,958
<i>We think that love</i>
<i>will make us whole...</i>

23
00:02:47,668 --> 00:02:50,087
<i>but the truth is, it'll ruin our lives.</i>

24
00:02:51,463 --> 00:02:53,299
<i>What's the point of all this?</i>

25
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:00,097
Teo!

26
00:03:08,439 --> 00:03:09,565
Yana!

27
00:03:24,330 --> 00:03:25,706
Yana!

28
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:39,321
You can drop us off here.

29
00:04:39,405 --> 00:04:42,241
Marlon, just turn the car around
if it's not allowed to park here.

30
00:04:42,324 --> 00:04:43,951
- Pa, watch your step.
- Come back for us.

31
00:04:44,368 --> 00:04:45,577
Help your brother.

32
00:04:46,954 --> 00:04:47,830
Thank you.

33
00:04:48,414 --> 00:04:50,249
- Pa, don't forget, okay?
- Take care.

34
00:04:50,332 --> 00:04:53,627
Always take your meds
and don't eat anything you shouldn't.

35
00:04:53,711 --> 00:04:55,629
I'll keep an eye on Papa.

36
00:04:55,713 --> 00:04:57,297
Leave it to me. I got it handled.

37
00:04:57,881 --> 00:05:00,676
I guess we can't stop you
from leaving, can we?

38
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:03,470
No, Pa.
I've already postponed leaving for a year.

39
00:05:03,554 --> 00:05:04,638
I can't waste any more time.

40
00:05:04,722 --> 00:05:06,682
Always keep your cool, okay?

41
00:05:06,765 --> 00:05:07,725
Don't get into fights.

42
00:05:07,808 --> 00:05:09,143
As long as they don't pull
a fast one on me

43
00:05:09,226 --> 00:05:11,145
and put my family at a disadvantage.

44
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,439
We're poor, but we won't let
people trample on us.

45
00:05:14,982 --> 00:05:16,275
I'll just work there,

46
00:05:16,358 --> 00:05:18,736
and when I get back,
we'll have a good life.

47
00:05:23,365 --> 00:05:25,617
- Silly Ronnie.
- Why?

48
00:05:25,701 --> 00:05:28,037
He gave me Larajean's address in Morocco.

49
00:05:28,495 --> 00:05:31,123
Are you going to see her?
Didn't she ghost you?

50
00:05:31,206 --> 00:05:33,792
Stop hunting for ghosts.

51
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:35,627
Forget about that woman.

52
00:05:35,711 --> 00:05:39,423
Just focus on your job and on yourself.

53
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:43,510
And don't be like Mama
who never came back.

54
00:05:44,511 --> 00:05:46,472
Of course. You know I can't leave you.

55
00:05:46,555 --> 00:05:48,557
Oh, I almost forgot.

56
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,392
- What's that?
- I made it for you...

57
00:05:50,476 --> 00:05:53,771
so you can take me with you
wherever you are.

58
00:05:54,438 --> 00:05:56,523
Oh, let's not forget something important.

59
00:05:56,607 --> 00:05:58,484
This one.

60
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:02,863
What's this?
Is this your foot or a duck's?

61
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:04,448
Hey.

62
00:06:05,282 --> 00:06:07,076
- I have to go.
- Bye.

63
00:06:07,159 --> 00:06:09,495
- You know my shoe size, right?
- I got you, Pa.

64
00:06:09,578 --> 00:06:10,746
- Take care!
- Bye!

65
00:06:10,829 --> 00:06:11,705
- God bless!
- Love you!

66
00:06:11,789 --> 00:06:13,665
- Love you!
- Love you!

67
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:19,671
Thank you.

68
00:06:24,093 --> 00:06:27,012


69
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:33,435


70
00:06:40,984 --> 00:06:42,319
Hello.

71
00:06:42,903 --> 00:06:43,737
Peace be with you.

72
00:06:43,821 --> 00:06:44,863
- Hello.
Where are you going?

73
00:06:44,947 --> 00:06:46,281
- Mhamid 9.
Mhamid 9.

74
00:06:46,365 --> 00:06:48,075
- Where are you from?
Philippines.

75
00:06:48,158 --> 00:06:50,327
Philippines! Oh, welcome to
Marrakech, <i>Khouya!</i>

76
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:51,620
<i>- Khouya?</i>
Yes, <i>Khouya.</i>

77
00:06:51,703 --> 00:06:52,955
Eighty dirhams to Mhamid 9.

78
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:54,498
- Eighty?
Yes.

79
00:06:54,581 --> 00:06:56,125
- Wait.
Yeah. Okay.

80
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:57,584
Eighty...

81
00:07:00,379 --> 00:07:01,463
- Eighty?
Yes.

82
00:07:01,547 --> 00:07:02,840
- Okay, 80.
- Okay.

83
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:03,799
Thank you.

84
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:06,009


85
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:42,629


86
00:07:50,095 --> 00:07:52,097


87
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,060


88
00:08:37,935 --> 00:08:40,395


89
00:08:44,107 --> 00:08:45,317
Gimo.

90
00:08:46,068 --> 00:08:48,028
Okay, now walk away.
Double time.

91
00:08:54,576 --> 00:08:57,079
Leon, don't just stand there.

92
00:08:57,162 --> 00:08:59,456
Move. Stall number eight.
Group of tourists. Go!

93
00:09:03,794 --> 00:09:06,588


94
00:09:11,009 --> 00:09:13,887


95
00:09:30,654 --> 00:09:32,656


96
00:09:45,961 --> 00:09:48,797


97
00:10:46,355 --> 00:10:48,398


98
00:11:02,454 --> 00:11:03,413
My wallet's been stolen!

99
00:11:03,497 --> 00:11:05,040
- Me too!
- Police, police!

100
00:11:05,123 --> 00:11:07,876
Oh, me too! My wallet
has been stolen from my bag!

101
00:11:07,959 --> 00:11:13,173


102
00:11:13,256 --> 00:11:15,384
Sir! Sir!

103
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:17,427
I lost my wallet. I lost my wallet too.

104
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:09,396
Red Spice.

105
00:12:43,138 --> 00:12:44,139
Carlos.

106
00:12:49,936 --> 00:12:51,146
Chameleon.

107
00:12:52,147 --> 00:12:53,690
My Chameleon...

108
00:13:00,614 --> 00:13:01,615
Good...

109
00:13:01,698 --> 00:13:03,116
Good, Chameleon.

110
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,451
Good.

111
00:13:05,577 --> 00:13:06,536
Good.

112
00:13:10,248 --> 00:13:11,583
Here.

113
00:13:19,090 --> 00:13:20,550
This is real. One carat.

114
00:13:20,634 --> 00:13:21,593
This?

115
00:13:25,347 --> 00:13:27,432
This one is fake. It's just glass.

116
00:13:27,516 --> 00:13:28,391
Very good.

117
00:13:33,396 --> 00:13:34,481
Come here.

118
00:13:43,949 --> 00:13:45,367
This is your prize...

119
00:13:46,117 --> 00:13:49,204
then give me mine.

120
00:13:54,209 --> 00:13:55,085
Boss.

121
00:14:03,385 --> 00:14:04,553
Next!

122
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:09,975
Move.

123
00:14:20,110 --> 00:14:21,695
Open your mouth.

124
00:14:26,032 --> 00:14:27,242
Open your mouth!

125
00:14:28,451 --> 00:14:29,661
Open your mouth!

126
00:14:39,796 --> 00:14:41,047
Boss. Boss...

127
00:14:42,757 --> 00:14:44,718
This is beautiful.

128
00:14:46,011 --> 00:14:47,012
Boss.

129
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:58,607
Please, please, boss!

130
00:14:58,690 --> 00:14:59,649
I'm sorry.

131
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:01,568
Please...

132
00:15:13,788 --> 00:15:16,207
Is this all we've got? Huh?

133
00:15:16,291 --> 00:15:18,293
I want more! This isn't enough!

134
00:15:20,337 --> 00:15:21,504
Next!

135
00:15:29,012 --> 00:15:29,888
Good!

136
00:15:31,348 --> 00:15:32,641
But it could be better.

137
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:35,769
- Understand?
- Yes, boss.

138
00:15:43,276 --> 00:15:44,861
Damn that Khaled!

139
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:47,113
I've already dodged
so many cases in Spain.

140
00:15:47,197 --> 00:15:48,990
I'm going to get even with that bastard.

141
00:15:49,741 --> 00:15:52,744
That's why you lost your ear.
You don't think.

142
00:15:52,827 --> 00:15:54,329
Fine. What's your plan?

143
00:15:54,412 --> 00:15:56,331
- I'll make one.
- Yeah, right!

144
00:15:56,414 --> 00:15:58,083
I'm getting revenge on him.

145
00:15:58,166 --> 00:15:59,334
Yana.

146
00:16:00,335 --> 00:16:03,171
Let's go through with our plan.
Let's escape!

147
00:16:03,254 --> 00:16:05,173
Diane, we're not ready.

148
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:07,634
We don't even have passports yet,
or any money.

149
00:16:07,717 --> 00:16:09,636
How far do you think
what we have will get us?

150
00:16:09,719 --> 00:16:11,971
We'll figure it out when we get there.

151
00:16:12,055 --> 00:16:14,849
Exactly. What matters is we get away now.

152
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:17,769
If we're not leaving Morocco,
what's the point?

153
00:16:17,852 --> 00:16:20,814
We're just like rats hiding
and running from those demons.

154
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:37,247
Here.

155
00:16:38,415 --> 00:16:40,125
Take your share.

156
00:16:41,835 --> 00:16:44,295
You go ahead. Continue the plan.

157
00:16:45,714 --> 00:16:46,715
What about you?

158
00:16:47,757 --> 00:16:49,592
I can't leave Mama.

159
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:52,887
Let's just keep in touch, okay?

160
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:55,390
Take care.

161
00:16:56,933 --> 00:16:59,144
Promise me we'll see each other again.

162
00:17:13,324 --> 00:17:14,993
You're exhausting!
Do whatever you want!

163
00:17:15,076 --> 00:17:16,202
Oh, you want to break up?

164
00:17:16,286 --> 00:17:17,579
You think I can't live without you?

165
00:17:17,662 --> 00:17:19,289
The kids stay with me!

166
00:17:19,372 --> 00:17:20,957
I'm tired of you!

167
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:23,334
I'll have my mother pick them up!

168
00:17:23,418 --> 00:17:26,880
I'll handle it! I'm done! Enough!

169
00:17:31,801 --> 00:17:33,762
- Good evening.
- Hey, bro!

170
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:35,805
Welcome! Welcome!

171
00:17:35,889 --> 00:17:37,849
I'm Jepoy, from Pangasinan.

172
00:17:38,391 --> 00:17:40,643
- Come in, come in.
- Oh, thank you.

173
00:17:40,727 --> 00:17:42,645
Relax first. Whew!

174
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:45,231
I work as a doorman at a hotel.

175
00:17:45,315 --> 00:17:46,858
Hey, bro, I'm Mike.

176
00:17:46,941 --> 00:17:48,735
- Mike.
- From Cebu. I'm a waiter.

177
00:17:49,486 --> 00:17:51,821
The guy you bumped into earlier,
the one who was mad,

178
00:17:51,905 --> 00:17:55,408
that's Boyet, from Cavite.
He works in housekeeping.

179
00:17:55,492 --> 00:17:56,743
Sorry about that.

180
00:17:56,826 --> 00:17:58,578
He's just fighting with his wife.

181
00:17:59,245 --> 00:18:01,956
Bro, how are you? I'm June, from Tarlac.

182
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:05,251
- Want some coffee or water?
- No, I'm good. Thanks.

183
00:18:05,335 --> 00:18:06,336
I'm Teo.

184
00:18:06,419 --> 00:18:08,755
I work maintenance at Jardin de Soleil.

185
00:18:08,838 --> 00:18:10,548
- Me too!
- Really?

186
00:18:10,632 --> 00:18:12,926
Yes!
I've been working there for years!

187
00:18:13,009 --> 00:18:14,427
Come on.

188
00:18:14,511 --> 00:18:17,263
Come with me to Spain.

189
00:18:17,347 --> 00:18:18,598
Diane, I'm sorry.

190
00:18:19,182 --> 00:18:21,226
I've already run from
too many cases in Spain.

191
00:18:21,309 --> 00:18:24,062
I can't go back there anymore.

192
00:18:29,234 --> 00:18:30,735
We just have to endure a bit longer.

193
00:18:33,238 --> 00:18:36,282
Yeah. We'll wait for you.

194
00:18:38,576 --> 00:18:40,912
Hey, are you part
of the Filipino group chat

195
00:18:40,995 --> 00:18:42,622
here in Morocco?

196
00:18:43,331 --> 00:18:46,417
Did you know there are only
about 50 Filipinos here in Marrakech?

197
00:18:46,501 --> 00:18:47,961
Oh, not yet.

198
00:18:48,044 --> 00:18:49,379
I'll add you.

199
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:53,091
- My number. Will this do?
- Yeah, that's fine.

200
00:18:53,174 --> 00:18:54,217
This helps a lot.

201
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:56,261
You'll have support when problems come up.

202
00:18:56,344 --> 00:18:59,514
Mm-hmm. Speaking of problems,
I got pickpocketed earlier.

203
00:19:00,598 --> 00:19:04,018
They took my passport and my dirhams.

204
00:19:04,102 --> 00:19:05,311
<i>Oh, no.</i>

205
00:19:07,021 --> 00:19:08,815
<i>Did you report it to the police?</i>

206
00:19:08,898 --> 00:19:10,775
They said they'd contact me.

207
00:19:10,859 --> 00:19:13,403
Bro, don't expect to get it back.

208
00:19:13,486 --> 00:19:17,448
Report it to the embassy in Rabat
and get a new passport.

209
00:19:17,532 --> 00:19:19,534
Be careful with pickpockets.

210
00:19:19,617 --> 00:19:21,452
- They're notorious here.
- Exactly.

211
00:19:21,536 --> 00:19:25,290
<i>But honestly, every country has them.</i>

212
00:19:25,373 --> 00:19:26,916
<i>Did you see who took it?</i>

213
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,919
- No.
- Do you have anything left?

214
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:36,968
Barely.

215
00:19:37,927 --> 00:19:39,679
I'll have to stretch it.

216
00:20:04,495 --> 00:20:05,914
- Ma?
- Yeah?

217
00:20:05,997 --> 00:20:08,583
- Where are you?
- I'm here.

218
00:20:12,503 --> 00:20:14,130
It's like a chimney in here!

219
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:15,465
Oh, hush! It's not that bad.

220
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:18,384
Stop it! You're being dramatic.

221
00:20:18,468 --> 00:20:20,845
I just want to remember
what it feels like.

222
00:20:20,929 --> 00:20:22,305
What if you get tempted?

223
00:20:22,388 --> 00:20:25,016
- Then I give in.
- You will not give in.

224
00:20:25,099 --> 00:20:26,768
My God, look at this kid.

225
00:20:26,851 --> 00:20:29,187
You know I don't have much time left.

226
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:31,648
Let me be. It's fun being
a sucker for this stuff.

227
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:36,069
I just want to be happy
before I end up in a coffin.

228
00:20:36,945 --> 00:20:38,905
That's so corny. You're not funny.

229
00:20:38,988 --> 00:20:41,366
What, are you in a hurry to leave me?

230
00:20:41,449 --> 00:20:46,746
I just want everything to be happy
when I say goodbye.

231
00:20:49,624 --> 00:20:51,000
And I want you, dear...

232
00:20:51,793 --> 00:20:55,421
to start a new life with your friends.

233
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:57,340
I want that too, Ma.

234
00:20:59,717 --> 00:21:01,886
Just a little more patience. Who knows...

235
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:04,722
maybe we'll hit it big someday.

236
00:21:04,806 --> 00:21:05,807
Right?

237
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:08,685
I know exactly how Khaled's mind works.

238
00:21:08,768 --> 00:21:10,103
He won't let you escape.

239
00:21:10,186 --> 00:21:11,980
- Then what about you?
- Easy.

240
00:21:12,063 --> 00:21:13,481
I'm old. I'm sick.

241
00:21:13,564 --> 00:21:15,566
- Oh, come on.
- Useless now.

242
00:21:21,906 --> 00:21:23,157
Ma...

243
00:21:23,825 --> 00:21:25,201
Stay strong.

244
00:21:26,703 --> 00:21:29,080
I'm going to change our lives.

245
00:21:57,191 --> 00:21:58,234
Sir?

246
00:21:59,694 --> 00:22:01,195
Sir Ibrahim? Sir? Okay.

247
00:22:02,238 --> 00:22:03,906
Yes, sir. I'll get back to you in an hour.

248
00:22:18,421 --> 00:22:20,214
- Is the battery new?
- Yes.

249
00:22:21,507 --> 00:22:23,468
I guess it's your lucky day, sir.

250
00:22:24,677 --> 00:22:28,431
'Cause I think the battery terminal
is just loose.

251
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:29,724
Yes.

252
00:22:34,854 --> 00:22:35,938
Voila!

253
00:22:36,022 --> 00:22:37,398
- All good?
- You're good to go, sir.

254
00:22:40,026 --> 00:22:42,111
Later I'll show you
the remittance center

255
00:22:42,195 --> 00:22:44,030
and where to buy cheap stuff.

256
00:22:44,113 --> 00:22:45,615
- We can walk around too.
- What?

257
00:22:45,698 --> 00:22:47,408
- Walk around!
- Hot dog.

258
00:22:47,492 --> 00:22:48,951
You're something else.

259
00:22:49,035 --> 00:22:52,038
Of course you'll tour me,
you've been here longer.

260
00:22:52,121 --> 00:22:54,832
There's a lot of stuff here, cheap...

261
00:22:54,916 --> 00:22:57,460
- Women again?
- Not that!

262
00:23:03,091 --> 00:23:06,052
Bro, if you buy something here,
make sure you haggle.

263
00:23:06,135 --> 00:23:09,222
If it's 100 dirhams, bring it down to 40.

264
00:23:10,098 --> 00:23:12,141
What about sandals or shoes?

265
00:23:12,225 --> 00:23:14,143
It depends. Leather's more expensive,

266
00:23:14,227 --> 00:23:16,479
but women's stuff is cheaper.

267
00:23:16,562 --> 00:23:18,106
Perfect.

268
00:23:18,189 --> 00:23:21,400
Just haggle hard,
even lowball if you have to.

269
00:23:22,568 --> 00:23:24,445
Hold on. I need to pee.

270
00:23:24,529 --> 00:23:27,365
- Sure. Be quick.
- Stay here. Yeah.

271
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:38,709
Excuse me.

272
00:23:41,838 --> 00:23:43,381
Miss!

273
00:23:43,464 --> 00:23:44,632
Miss!

274
00:23:44,715 --> 00:23:46,425
Miss? Miss.

275
00:23:47,260 --> 00:23:49,720
Miss! Miss!

276
00:23:49,804 --> 00:23:52,265
What's your problem?
That's not good.

277
00:23:52,348 --> 00:23:53,599
You stole my passport!

278
00:23:53,683 --> 00:23:55,393
I can't understand.

279
00:23:55,476 --> 00:23:56,769
You stole...

280
00:23:56,853 --> 00:23:58,396
You stole my wallet and my passport.

281
00:23:58,479 --> 00:24:00,314
No! No English!

282
00:24:04,986 --> 00:24:07,655
Miss! Where's my money?

283
00:24:07,738 --> 00:24:09,157
Go or I will call the police!

284
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:11,409
Police?
Yes, I will bring you to the police!

285
00:24:11,784 --> 00:24:13,452
No, no, no, no, no.

286
00:24:16,873 --> 00:24:19,041
- Wait, wait. Wait, wait, miss. Miss.
- Leave me alone!

287
00:24:19,125 --> 00:24:20,626
No, I just want my money, okay?

288
00:24:25,798 --> 00:24:27,008
Ah!

289
00:24:27,091 --> 00:24:29,886
I just want my money!
Give me my money back!

290
00:24:43,107 --> 00:24:47,862
<i>Hello? Hello!</i>
<i>Your mom is in the hospital!</i>

291
00:24:47,945 --> 00:24:49,322
You're Filipino?

292
00:24:53,534 --> 00:24:55,036
Miss! Miss!

293
00:25:51,634 --> 00:25:53,678
Your mother
needs to resume chemo

294
00:25:53,761 --> 00:25:55,554
and radiation immediately.

295
00:25:55,638 --> 00:25:56,806
Will she recover?

296
00:25:56,889 --> 00:25:59,725
We'll know
after three more cycles.

297
00:25:59,809 --> 00:26:00,935
Then we'll do scans
and see how she responds.

298
00:26:01,018 --> 00:26:03,396
Every delay complicates her situation.

299
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:05,815
Thank you.

300
00:26:48,441 --> 00:26:49,775
You're still following me?

301
00:26:49,859 --> 00:26:51,986
Stop pretending.
I know you're Filipino.

302
00:26:52,069 --> 00:26:52,987
You're crazy!

303
00:26:53,070 --> 00:26:54,905
Miss, come on,
let's not play games.

304
00:26:56,449 --> 00:26:58,200
I know you're struggling.

305
00:26:58,701 --> 00:26:59,869
What happened to your mom?

306
00:27:03,789 --> 00:27:05,416
You won't talk?

307
00:27:05,499 --> 00:27:07,251
Fine, the money you took--

308
00:27:07,335 --> 00:27:08,711
I just needed it.

309
00:27:11,047 --> 00:27:13,382
My mom has stage four lung cancer.

310
00:27:14,675 --> 00:27:15,885
So you steal?

311
00:27:16,761 --> 00:27:18,637
You couldn't find a proper job?

312
00:27:18,721 --> 00:27:21,015
I go where there's money.

313
00:27:21,098 --> 00:27:23,059
We both need to earn.

314
00:27:23,893 --> 00:27:25,353
Look, you almost stabbed me earlier--

315
00:27:25,436 --> 00:27:27,146
But I didn't.

316
00:27:27,813 --> 00:27:29,565
Explain that at the police station.

317
00:27:29,648 --> 00:27:31,609
Wait, please.

318
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:37,365
Because...

319
00:27:37,448 --> 00:27:40,409
my mother really needs me.

320
00:27:42,036 --> 00:27:44,121
I don't know what to do anymore.

321
00:27:45,289 --> 00:27:47,416
I'm exhausted.

322
00:27:50,336 --> 00:27:52,129
Then why give this back?

323
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:55,925
I know what it's like
to have a sick family member.

324
00:27:56,300 --> 00:27:58,010
I spent my whole life fighting that.

325
00:27:58,094 --> 00:27:59,637
But I never stole.

326
00:28:00,763 --> 00:28:02,139
That's because you're kind.

327
00:28:03,099 --> 00:28:04,350
We're not the same.

328
00:28:10,106 --> 00:28:12,191
Just don't turn me in.

329
00:28:14,026 --> 00:28:15,361
I promise...

330
00:28:15,986 --> 00:28:17,863
I'll return your money...

331
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:20,324
Mateo.

332
00:28:21,409 --> 00:28:22,785
Mateo Crisanto.

333
00:28:25,246 --> 00:28:26,705
It's on your passport.

334
00:28:29,583 --> 00:28:31,502
You're not even going to apologize?

335
00:28:31,585 --> 00:28:33,087
I said it already.

336
00:28:33,587 --> 00:28:35,464
I'll return what I took.

337
00:28:35,548 --> 00:28:37,758
- Make sure you do--
- Yana Kassir.

338
00:28:38,676 --> 00:28:40,428
That's my name.

339
00:28:50,104 --> 00:28:51,063
Hey, bro, how are you?

340
00:28:51,147 --> 00:28:52,398
I'm okay.

341
00:28:53,149 --> 00:28:55,067
Ronnie, what's Larajean's address again?

342
00:28:55,651 --> 00:28:57,361
I thought you weren't going there anymore.

343
00:28:57,445 --> 00:28:59,029
I lost it.

344
00:28:59,113 --> 00:29:01,782
Oh, here we go. Missing her again, huh?

345
00:29:01,866 --> 00:29:04,201
Idiot. No. Just checking in.

346
00:29:04,285 --> 00:29:05,536
Yeah, right.

347
00:29:06,579 --> 00:29:09,832
Twenty-five La Belle, Marrakech, Morocco.

348
00:29:09,915 --> 00:29:10,791
That's it.

349
00:29:10,875 --> 00:29:11,876
Got it. Thanks, Ronnie.

350
00:29:11,959 --> 00:29:13,043
Take care, bro!

351
00:29:21,635 --> 00:29:24,680
Tawabel Pizza! Delivery!

352
00:29:26,307 --> 00:29:30,269
Tawabel Pizza delivery
for Bellisimos Apartment!

353
00:29:30,352 --> 00:29:33,397
Bellisimos? You mean La Belle?

354
00:29:33,481 --> 00:29:37,151
Oh! No, no, no. Bellisimos Apartment.

355
00:29:37,234 --> 00:29:39,487
No Bellisimos Apartment, only La Belle.

356
00:29:39,570 --> 00:29:41,864
- This one.
- Oh, okay, okay.

357
00:29:41,947 --> 00:29:44,366
- Street there?
- Yes.

358
00:29:46,660 --> 00:29:48,412
Do you have a glass of water?

359
00:29:49,997 --> 00:29:52,082
It's so hot. Please.

360
00:29:52,166 --> 00:29:54,543
- Wait here.
- Okay, thank you.

361
00:31:06,865 --> 00:31:07,908
Teo?

362
00:31:10,869 --> 00:31:12,079
What are you doing here?

363
00:31:14,206 --> 00:31:15,207
Here?

364
00:31:16,250 --> 00:31:17,167
Working.

365
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:21,589
That was the plan, right?
You just left the country first.

366
00:31:25,175 --> 00:31:26,176
How are you doing?

367
00:31:31,515 --> 00:31:32,766
Your place is huge.

368
00:31:33,267 --> 00:31:35,269
- I'll take a look around.
- T... Teo...

369
00:31:35,352 --> 00:31:36,437
I'll just look around.

370
00:31:38,147 --> 00:31:39,231
Wow.

371
00:31:40,441 --> 00:31:42,484
- It's beautiful.
- Wait a minute.

372
00:31:42,568 --> 00:31:43,861
Wait a minute.

373
00:31:43,944 --> 00:31:44,987
Did we fight?

374
00:31:46,071 --> 00:31:47,489
I don't remember.

375
00:31:47,573 --> 00:31:48,866
You suddenly blocked me.

376
00:31:48,949 --> 00:31:51,827
And then you didn't respond
to my calls and messages.

377
00:31:51,910 --> 00:31:54,163
Let's talk about this on a different day.

378
00:31:54,246 --> 00:31:58,125
Because... because my boss
will come home soon.

379
00:31:58,208 --> 00:31:59,585
Why are you freaking out?

380
00:31:59,668 --> 00:32:00,753
Teo...

381
00:32:02,630 --> 00:32:03,547
Teo, go home.

382
00:32:03,631 --> 00:32:05,507
You're in too much of a hurry.

383
00:32:17,728 --> 00:32:20,648
Tell your boss that
your boyfriend came to visit you.

384
00:32:22,149 --> 00:32:23,108
Ex-boyfriend.

385
00:32:24,026 --> 00:32:25,653
Is it an ex-boyfriend?
I don't really know.

386
00:32:25,736 --> 00:32:27,863
- Teo, please--
- Introduce me as anything.

387
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:29,490
I might get a job out of it, who knows?

388
00:32:29,573 --> 00:32:31,450
- Please...
- Please what?

389
00:32:32,534 --> 00:32:34,828
Larajean, I never did
anything wrong to you.

390
00:32:35,537 --> 00:32:38,165
There is only one reason
why you did this to me.

391
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:43,837
Is this him?

392
00:32:44,922 --> 00:32:46,632
You've got to go home, Teo.

393
00:32:47,633 --> 00:32:50,969
Actually, just a few months
after you left, I knew.

394
00:32:51,053 --> 00:32:52,096
I felt it.

395
00:32:53,806 --> 00:32:55,224
I wish you had been honest.

396
00:32:55,307 --> 00:32:59,853
I may have fallen short
because of my family's needs,

397
00:32:59,937 --> 00:33:01,271
but I never cheated on you.

398
00:33:01,355 --> 00:33:03,357
I didn't run away from you,
and vanish into thin air.

399
00:33:04,149 --> 00:33:05,275
All right, I get it.

400
00:33:05,359 --> 00:33:06,735
Could you please leave?

401
00:33:06,819 --> 00:33:08,028
Just leave, please.

402
00:33:08,112 --> 00:33:09,405
Larajean!

403
00:33:10,698 --> 00:33:13,951
- Larajean!
- Teo... leave here.

404
00:33:14,034 --> 00:33:16,120
- Please, just go.
- What? I'll leave there.

405
00:33:16,203 --> 00:33:18,414
- Teo, I'm begging you.
- No, I'm leaving there.

406
00:33:18,497 --> 00:33:20,541
- No, I'll stay here then.
- Teo, please!

407
00:33:21,542 --> 00:33:23,377
Who are you?
You're messing with my girl!

408
00:33:23,460 --> 00:33:25,212
No! No, no, no... um...

409
00:33:25,295 --> 00:33:26,797
No, I'm not messing with your girl.

410
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,132
She's yours.

411
00:33:28,215 --> 00:33:30,092
You're cheating on me, Larajean?

412
00:33:30,175 --> 00:33:31,301
You slut!

413
00:33:31,385 --> 00:33:32,720
Hey!

414
00:33:32,803 --> 00:33:34,346
Hey!

415
00:33:34,430 --> 00:33:35,556
Teo!

416
00:33:35,639 --> 00:33:37,766
Teo, that's enough! That's enough!

417
00:33:38,434 --> 00:33:39,351
What did you say?

418
00:33:39,435 --> 00:33:40,686
Teo! That's enough!

419
00:33:40,769 --> 00:33:43,605
Teo, that's enough! Just leave! Leave!

420
00:33:43,689 --> 00:33:44,940
Larajean, he'll kill you!

421
00:33:45,023 --> 00:33:46,734
I can handle myself. Just leave!

422
00:33:46,817 --> 00:33:47,735
And don't blame me.

423
00:33:47,818 --> 00:33:50,028
It was you who went back on your word.

424
00:33:50,112 --> 00:33:51,280
You know the reason, don't you?

425
00:33:51,363 --> 00:33:52,823
Yes! That you ended up in jail

426
00:33:52,906 --> 00:33:54,825
the day you were meant to join me here.

427
00:33:56,076 --> 00:33:57,745
You nearly killed--

428
00:33:57,828 --> 00:34:00,456
Because I was defending my father.
Is that wrong?

429
00:34:00,539 --> 00:34:02,082
You're great when it comes to your family!

430
00:34:02,166 --> 00:34:03,917
But you always put me in danger!

431
00:34:04,001 --> 00:34:05,961
Look at what you've done now!
You're causing trouble!

432
00:34:06,044 --> 00:34:07,254
I didn't mean to bother you

433
00:34:07,337 --> 00:34:08,422
because I've felt this
for a long time now.

434
00:34:08,505 --> 00:34:09,882
This relationship has been over
for a long time now!

435
00:34:10,966 --> 00:34:13,802
I just made sure
so we wouldn't have any regrets!

436
00:34:13,886 --> 00:34:15,179
I'm not stupid, Larajean.

437
00:34:16,764 --> 00:34:18,307
But still, thank you for everything.

438
00:34:18,807 --> 00:34:20,184
- Goodbye.
- Teo...

439
00:34:22,311 --> 00:34:23,979
- You animal!
- What?

440
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:24,938
- I will call the police!
- What?

441
00:34:25,022 --> 00:34:27,107
- Just go!
- He won't file a complaint!

442
00:34:27,191 --> 00:34:29,568
Living together without being married
is prohibited here.

443
00:34:29,651 --> 00:34:32,821
We live together,
but you'll go to jail for harassment!

444
00:34:32,905 --> 00:34:35,282
You'll be in jail too! Leave now!

445
00:34:37,201 --> 00:34:38,118
I'll call the police!

446
00:34:38,202 --> 00:34:39,203
Let's go.

447
00:34:41,371 --> 00:34:42,664
- I'll drive.
- No, I'll do it.

448
00:34:42,748 --> 00:34:43,916
I'll do it.

449
00:34:44,416 --> 00:34:45,417
Stop it!

450
00:34:56,929 --> 00:34:58,180
Wow.

451
00:35:05,312 --> 00:35:06,897
You're unbelievable.

452
00:35:07,481 --> 00:35:09,441
- You are also intense.
- Why?

453
00:35:09,525 --> 00:35:10,651
Can you believe it?

454
00:35:10,734 --> 00:35:12,820
You're willing to go to jail for a woman.

455
00:35:15,697 --> 00:35:17,407
What were you doing there?

456
00:35:17,491 --> 00:35:18,992
I was delivering something.
Isn't it obvious?

457
00:35:19,076 --> 00:35:22,079
So, what's going on? Come on, tell me.

458
00:35:23,413 --> 00:35:25,249
How much do you love that girl?

459
00:35:28,126 --> 00:35:29,461
How much do I love her?

460
00:35:33,423 --> 00:35:35,425
- Before...
- What?

461
00:35:35,509 --> 00:35:36,760
I thought she was the one.

462
00:35:38,679 --> 00:35:40,806
I thought we'd end up together, but...

463
00:35:41,765 --> 00:35:43,267
things between us became uncertain.

464
00:35:43,684 --> 00:35:45,060
Turns out, we weren't stable enough.

465
00:35:46,061 --> 00:35:47,437
We never shared a deep connection.

466
00:35:48,480 --> 00:35:50,357
That's why even back then,
I already accepted it.

467
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:52,401
- Do you still love her?
- Of course not!

468
00:35:52,484 --> 00:35:54,152
- Really?
- Not anymore.

469
00:35:54,236 --> 00:35:56,113
That whole love nonsense...

470
00:35:56,488 --> 00:35:59,074
will eventually crush you.
Especially if...

471
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:00,617
it's not with the right person.

472
00:36:02,619 --> 00:36:05,330
Does that even exist? "The One"?

473
00:36:05,414 --> 00:36:06,915
Teo.

474
00:36:08,375 --> 00:36:09,793
- Look.
- You need to take a dump?

475
00:36:09,877 --> 00:36:11,169
Nope.

476
00:36:11,253 --> 00:36:13,589
- What you said gave me chills.
- You're that disgusted?

477
00:36:13,672 --> 00:36:14,965
Absolutely!

478
00:36:15,048 --> 00:36:16,633
You've never dated
anyone before, have you?

479
00:36:18,343 --> 00:36:19,428
Have you ever been in love?

480
00:36:20,012 --> 00:36:21,471
Have you ever gotten your feelings hurt?

481
00:36:21,972 --> 00:36:23,640
And why would I tell you that?

482
00:36:24,683 --> 00:36:26,768
So stingy! And here I am,
being open with you.

483
00:36:29,271 --> 00:36:30,439
But, Teo...

484
00:36:30,856 --> 00:36:32,107
come to think of it...

485
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:35,611
there are eight billion people
in this world.

486
00:36:35,694 --> 00:36:36,945
Mm-hmm?

487
00:36:37,362 --> 00:36:39,573
I'm pretty sure
there's one person for you.

488
00:36:40,324 --> 00:36:41,199
Right?

489
00:36:43,619 --> 00:36:46,288
- What if there isn't?
- You're the problem, then.

490
00:37:04,598 --> 00:37:05,682
Why are you looking at me like that?

491
00:37:05,766 --> 00:37:07,225
- Why?
- Stop. Let's go.

492
00:37:08,226 --> 00:37:09,311
- Let's go.
- I'll drive.

493
00:37:09,394 --> 00:37:11,313
What do you mean you'll drive?
It's my bike.

494
00:37:11,396 --> 00:37:13,315
- I'll drive.
- Let me do it, just get on.

495
00:37:13,398 --> 00:37:14,983
Stop hijacking my bike.

496
00:37:15,067 --> 00:37:16,485
This is the only way I can repay you.

497
00:37:21,531 --> 00:37:22,449
I think it's gone.

498
00:37:23,158 --> 00:37:24,242
The what?

499
00:37:25,327 --> 00:37:28,372
The pain. It's as if the wind
just carried it away.

500
00:37:29,498 --> 00:37:30,958
This was all I needed.

501
00:37:32,125 --> 00:37:33,460
Go faster.

502
00:37:34,086 --> 00:37:35,504
Hold on!

503
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:08,203
That's a lot.

504
00:38:10,288 --> 00:38:11,707
Is someone knocking?
Do you have a visitor?

505
00:38:11,790 --> 00:38:13,166
No.

506
00:38:13,250 --> 00:38:15,252
Hold on. Don't open the door!

507
00:38:18,964 --> 00:38:22,009
- Surprise!
- Who's that? Oh, come in!

508
00:38:22,092 --> 00:38:23,844
- Who are you?
- Oh, hello!

509
00:38:23,927 --> 00:38:26,346
- I'm Teo, Yana's friend.
- Teo!

510
00:38:26,430 --> 00:38:29,141
A friend. My name's Nadia.

511
00:38:29,599 --> 00:38:33,478
You can call me Auntie Nadia,
Ms. Nadia...

512
00:38:34,062 --> 00:38:36,023
- Mommy Nadia--
- Ma!

513
00:38:36,606 --> 00:38:37,441
Mommy...

514
00:38:37,524 --> 00:38:40,027
I brought something for you!

515
00:38:40,110 --> 00:38:41,653
I brought fruit. You might like it.

516
00:38:41,737 --> 00:38:43,905
Really? Oh, that's a lot!

517
00:38:43,989 --> 00:38:45,699
- Grapes...
- Yana, look! It's a lot!

518
00:38:45,782 --> 00:38:48,910
I bought it at the grocery store.
There's... this too.

519
00:38:48,994 --> 00:38:51,955
Come on, sit down. Sit down.

520
00:38:52,581 --> 00:38:53,874
Are you new here?

521
00:38:53,957 --> 00:38:56,501
Are you a tourist? OFW?

522
00:38:56,585 --> 00:38:58,295
Ah, first time, OFW.

523
00:38:58,378 --> 00:39:00,839
I do maintenance
over at Hotel de Soleil.

524
00:39:00,922 --> 00:39:03,341
Did you get culture shock here in Morocco?

525
00:39:03,425 --> 00:39:05,761
But I'm getting used to it.

526
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:08,805
- Are you single?
- Ma!

527
00:39:08,889 --> 00:39:11,683
- I'm just getting to know him!
- You shouldn't ask that!

528
00:39:11,767 --> 00:39:12,934
Shh!

529
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:15,937
You must have really good genes, huh?

530
00:39:17,773 --> 00:39:19,399
Ma, that's enough. Enough!

531
00:39:19,483 --> 00:39:20,567
Would you like some <i>Harira?</i>

532
00:39:20,650 --> 00:39:22,569
- Huh?
- It's delicious. It's soup!

533
00:39:22,652 --> 00:39:25,530
<i>Harira. </i>My daughter cooked that.

534
00:39:25,614 --> 00:39:27,449
- Yana is a great cook!
- All right!

535
00:39:27,532 --> 00:39:29,367
- Sit down.
- Okay!

536
00:39:29,451 --> 00:39:31,453
- Come on. Sit down.
- Here.

537
00:39:34,122 --> 00:39:36,666
Um... I'll go ahead and give it a try.

538
00:39:40,587 --> 00:39:41,713
Wow!

539
00:39:42,297 --> 00:39:43,757
- It's so good!
- Mm-hmm!

540
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:45,133
- You cooked this?
- Yeah.

541
00:39:45,217 --> 00:39:46,593
She's a great cook.

542
00:39:46,676 --> 00:39:48,595
- She's wife material.
- You're right!

543
00:39:50,764 --> 00:39:52,182
I'm so full!

544
00:39:52,265 --> 00:39:53,934
I can't move, Mama!

545
00:39:54,518 --> 00:39:57,229
Thank you.
Yana's such a good cook, isn't she?

546
00:39:57,312 --> 00:39:58,396
Yes, absolutely.

547
00:39:58,480 --> 00:40:00,607
Teo said that you're a great cook!

548
00:40:00,690 --> 00:40:01,858
I heard it.

549
00:40:01,942 --> 00:40:03,360
Here. Water.

550
00:40:03,443 --> 00:40:05,153
- Right. Thank you.
- Thank you.

551
00:40:05,237 --> 00:40:06,571
Not that. That's too sweet.

552
00:40:09,950 --> 00:40:12,410
But... thanks.

553
00:40:13,203 --> 00:40:14,287
That's a lot.

554
00:40:14,371 --> 00:40:16,790
I forgot to ask you
what your mom isn't allowed to have.

555
00:40:16,873 --> 00:40:19,334
- Gosh.
- Looks like she loved it all.

556
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:22,420
She'll eat anything,
even if it's bad for her.

557
00:40:22,504 --> 00:40:24,297
- Hmm.
- Hmm?

558
00:40:24,381 --> 00:40:25,841
She's just like my dad.
He can't have soft drinks,

559
00:40:25,924 --> 00:40:28,552
- but drinks them anyway.
- He's just like her!

560
00:40:28,635 --> 00:40:30,095
She's not supposed to have sweets.

561
00:40:30,178 --> 00:40:31,847
Her cancer cells are so aggressive,

562
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:33,348
but she's just so stubborn.

563
00:40:33,431 --> 00:40:35,600
And, she even hides cigarettes.

564
00:40:35,684 --> 00:40:37,561
Go ahead, Yana. Gossip about me.

565
00:40:37,644 --> 00:40:39,980
- Go ahead and ruin me.
- She hates being called out.

566
00:40:40,063 --> 00:40:41,940
- Hey! I'm not sensitive!
- You are sensitive.

567
00:40:42,023 --> 00:40:44,401
Just like Dad. He doesn't like
being told what to do, either.

568
00:40:46,695 --> 00:40:48,405
So stubborn.

569
00:40:49,322 --> 00:40:50,991
- Just once in a while.
- No.

570
00:40:51,491 --> 00:40:52,909
Where's your father?

571
00:40:55,662 --> 00:40:56,830
Wow.

572
00:40:57,455 --> 00:40:59,082
So pretty.

573
00:40:59,583 --> 00:41:02,711
My dad is in Spain.

574
00:41:02,794 --> 00:41:04,087
Wow.

575
00:41:20,145 --> 00:41:22,355
How are you related to them?
Her specifically?

576
00:41:23,148 --> 00:41:24,399
Which one?

577
00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:25,817
The one next to you.

578
00:41:27,110 --> 00:41:28,737
Oh! That's...

579
00:41:28,820 --> 00:41:31,364
That's my co-worker, Rita! Rita...

580
00:41:32,532 --> 00:41:34,826
What's her last name again?
Rita... Rita Crisost...

581
00:41:34,910 --> 00:41:36,828
Rita, Rita...

582
00:41:36,912 --> 00:41:37,787
Crisanto.

583
00:41:38,413 --> 00:41:39,998
Wow! You're amazing!

584
00:41:40,081 --> 00:41:41,541
How did you know?

585
00:41:41,625 --> 00:41:43,251
We were so young there!

586
00:41:44,628 --> 00:41:46,213
Rita Crisanto...

587
00:41:49,841 --> 00:41:51,009
She's my mom.

588
00:42:00,060 --> 00:42:01,519
She works in Dubai.

589
00:42:01,603 --> 00:42:02,938
How did you get to know each other?

590
00:42:03,563 --> 00:42:04,564
Ah...

591
00:42:04,648 --> 00:42:06,566
I didn't work in Dubai.
I worked in Abu Dhabi.

592
00:42:06,650 --> 00:42:09,986
But we met here... in...

593
00:42:11,446 --> 00:42:12,864
Casablanca.

594
00:42:15,408 --> 00:42:18,119
It's been over ten years
since we last heard from her.

595
00:42:18,745 --> 00:42:21,373
She said she was in Dubai.
Turns out she's here in Morocco.

596
00:42:24,167 --> 00:42:25,919
Do you know how to get to her?

597
00:42:26,378 --> 00:42:27,295
Uh...

598
00:42:28,546 --> 00:42:29,673
Ah...

599
00:42:29,756 --> 00:42:32,592
When I left...

600
00:42:32,676 --> 00:42:35,595
Casablanca, I lost contact with her.

601
00:42:36,429 --> 00:42:39,140
She never mentioned her plans to you?

602
00:42:39,599 --> 00:42:41,768
Nothing.

603
00:42:41,851 --> 00:42:45,021
I didn't know she had a family
back in the Philippines.

604
00:42:52,904 --> 00:42:54,447
<i>You got accepted in Dubai?</i>

605
00:42:54,531 --> 00:42:55,991
You're just telling me now?

606
00:42:56,074 --> 00:42:57,659
I knew you wouldn't allow me.

607
00:42:57,742 --> 00:43:00,912
I absolutely won't allow it.
Issay is only a year old.

608
00:43:01,871 --> 00:43:05,917
You'll just leave your two kids behind?

609
00:43:06,001 --> 00:43:07,794
It's a waste of a good opportunity!

610
00:43:07,877 --> 00:43:10,088
I'm doing this for our family.

611
00:43:10,171 --> 00:43:11,923
I'll just leave for one or two years.

612
00:43:12,007 --> 00:43:14,342
Whatever. You're not leaving.

613
00:43:14,426 --> 00:43:15,885
Fine.

614
00:43:15,969 --> 00:43:17,887
Match what I'd be earning there.
Can you do that?

615
00:43:17,971 --> 00:43:20,223
Move Teo to a better school.

616
00:43:20,307 --> 00:43:22,475
Move us to a better home!

617
00:43:22,559 --> 00:43:24,060
You're mocking me,

618
00:43:24,144 --> 00:43:25,103
and you're throwing everything
I've done back in my face!

619
00:43:31,109 --> 00:43:33,028
You know, you are a liar.

620
00:43:33,111 --> 00:43:35,572
Word has been going around

621
00:43:35,655 --> 00:43:37,198
that you have a lover there!

622
00:43:37,490 --> 00:43:39,534
You've got a man in there! You liar!

623
00:43:52,297 --> 00:43:54,841
Pa! Pa!

624
00:43:54,924 --> 00:43:55,800
Pa, I'm so sorry!

625
00:44:04,184 --> 00:44:06,186
- Hello?
- This is Teo.

626
00:44:07,103 --> 00:44:08,521
Father is in the hospital.

627
00:44:08,605 --> 00:44:10,065
<i>Leg and foot were broken.</i>

628
00:44:10,148 --> 00:44:11,775
A machine fell on him.

629
00:44:11,858 --> 00:44:12,984
How is he?

630
00:44:13,068 --> 00:44:15,695
The doctor said he could walk, but...

631
00:44:17,280 --> 00:44:19,157
- he's crippled now.
- <i>Teo.</i>

632
00:44:19,240 --> 00:44:21,159
Take care of your sister, okay?

633
00:44:22,911 --> 00:44:24,913
Please, don't let anything
happen to Issay.

634
00:44:25,663 --> 00:44:28,291
This will... be the last time you'll call.

635
00:44:28,375 --> 00:44:30,335
- Why?
- Hey!

636
00:44:30,418 --> 00:44:31,544
<i>Who is that? Who is it?</i>

637
00:44:31,628 --> 00:44:33,380
Ma. Ma!

638
00:45:16,381 --> 00:45:17,215
Teo.

639
00:45:18,091 --> 00:45:19,551
I'm so sorry for your loss.

640
00:45:22,011 --> 00:45:23,179
You know what, Yana?

641
00:45:24,806 --> 00:45:25,807
You're lucky.

642
00:45:29,144 --> 00:45:32,522
Because even though
you and Ms. Nadia are struggling

643
00:45:32,605 --> 00:45:33,815
because of her illness

644
00:45:34,274 --> 00:45:36,985
she still makes you feel
that she loves you.

645
00:45:39,404 --> 00:45:40,905
But my mother here?

646
00:45:43,032 --> 00:45:43,908
I don't know.

647
00:45:51,416 --> 00:45:52,500
May God forgive me,

648
00:45:52,584 --> 00:45:54,627
but all I can say to her is...

649
00:45:56,796 --> 00:45:58,423
that she's a bad person.

650
00:46:00,300 --> 00:46:02,844
Teo, don't speak like that.

651
00:46:02,927 --> 00:46:05,722
We don't know what really happened to her.

652
00:46:05,805 --> 00:46:07,265
I don't care.

653
00:46:07,348 --> 00:46:09,309
It's clear to me that...

654
00:46:11,519 --> 00:46:12,937
she deceived us.

655
00:46:17,317 --> 00:46:18,401
She abandoned us.

656
00:46:22,822 --> 00:46:23,990
Replaced us.

657
00:46:28,036 --> 00:46:29,787
She was a bad wife.

658
00:46:30,914 --> 00:46:32,624
She was also a bad mother.

659
00:46:40,131 --> 00:46:42,008
Ten years is a long time.

660
00:46:45,220 --> 00:46:48,014
All along,
I'd only find her here.

661
00:46:54,312 --> 00:46:57,732
No one can tell how long
we'll be here on Earth.

662
00:46:58,983 --> 00:47:01,819
That's why we need to make
the most of our time together.

663
00:47:02,987 --> 00:47:04,197
What about her?

664
00:47:06,491 --> 00:47:09,494
Was she able to make the most
out of her life without us?

665
00:47:10,203 --> 00:47:11,579
Before she died...

666
00:47:13,706 --> 00:47:15,124
did she even think about us?

667
00:47:16,793 --> 00:47:18,002
Probably not.

668
00:47:21,422 --> 00:47:23,216
She definitely didn't.

669
00:47:34,018 --> 00:47:35,520
That's enough.

670
00:47:56,207 --> 00:47:57,625
Son!

671
00:47:57,709 --> 00:48:00,169
Don't worry about us here.
We're doing fine here.

672
00:48:00,253 --> 00:48:02,755
I'm sorry if this girl disturbed you.

673
00:48:02,839 --> 00:48:04,632
Give me that, Dad.
Let me talk to him first.

674
00:48:04,716 --> 00:48:07,302
Hello, Teo? It's Dad who
has a problem here, not me.

675
00:48:07,385 --> 00:48:10,305
<i>He doesn't want to see a doctor</i>
<i>when he said his feet feel numb already.</i>

676
00:48:10,388 --> 00:48:12,515
<i>Talk to Dad! He's being stubborn.</i>

677
00:48:12,599 --> 00:48:14,684
<i>Son, I finally got the car.</i>

678
00:48:15,310 --> 00:48:17,186
<i>Berto is really easy to talk to.</i>

679
00:48:17,270 --> 00:48:19,022
He even took me home.

680
00:48:19,105 --> 00:48:20,565
He didn't add any interest either.

681
00:48:21,190 --> 00:48:23,192
I checked the engine and...

682
00:48:23,484 --> 00:48:24,736
it's still working well!

683
00:48:26,487 --> 00:48:27,530
Son.

684
00:48:28,031 --> 00:48:29,449
Dad, I saw Mom.

685
00:48:30,033 --> 00:48:31,743
Is she with you there in Morocco?

686
00:48:32,994 --> 00:48:34,203
Yes.

687
00:48:34,287 --> 00:48:36,414
That's why we couldn't find her in Dubai

688
00:48:36,497 --> 00:48:38,207
<i>even though we asked the embassy for help.</i>

689
00:48:38,791 --> 00:48:40,501
It's because she's in Morocco.

690
00:48:40,585 --> 00:48:44,005
Tell her that she's a shameless jerk.

691
00:48:45,423 --> 00:48:47,008
She's already dead, Dad.

692
00:48:55,391 --> 00:48:56,934
<i>She's been dead for five years now.</i>

693
00:48:57,769 --> 00:48:58,770
<i>Here she is, Dad.</i>

694
00:49:04,817 --> 00:49:05,985
It's okay.

695
00:49:08,738 --> 00:49:11,324
We're already used to
not having her around, aren't we?

696
00:49:14,994 --> 00:49:16,204
All right.

697
00:49:16,579 --> 00:49:18,039
Take care, Dad.

698
00:49:36,849 --> 00:49:37,934
Where were you yesterday?

699
00:49:38,017 --> 00:49:38,893
I was calling your phone but no answer.

700
00:49:38,976 --> 00:49:40,103
I was working.

701
00:49:40,186 --> 00:49:41,604
I... I forget my phone.

702
00:49:41,688 --> 00:49:43,022
Fine. I have a job for you.

703
00:49:43,106 --> 00:49:44,816
But this one is not a very easy job.

704
00:49:44,899 --> 00:49:46,484
That's why I brought Diane to the hotel.

705
00:49:46,818 --> 00:49:47,902
Diane?

706
00:49:51,572 --> 00:49:53,449
So you already know
every corner of the hotel?

707
00:49:53,533 --> 00:49:54,784
Yes, boss.

708
00:49:58,830 --> 00:50:00,540
Sheikh Jamal is not
just married to royalty.

709
00:50:00,623 --> 00:50:01,958
He owns the largest gold and
precious stone mines in Morocco.

710
00:50:02,041 --> 00:50:04,585
<i>He will check in</i>
<i>at the Jardin de Soleil Hotel soon.</i>

711
00:50:04,711 --> 00:50:06,212
<i>There will be an event.</i>

712
00:50:06,713 --> 00:50:08,923
<i>He will stay at the Presidential Suite.</i>

713
00:50:09,006 --> 00:50:11,843
<i>He brings a lot of money and some jewelry</i>
<i>in his suite every time he checks in.</i>

714
00:50:11,926 --> 00:50:16,514
Bring me the Sheikh's money
and all of his valuables.

715
00:50:17,306 --> 00:50:18,433
Understand?

716
00:50:19,392 --> 00:50:20,518
You may go.

717
00:50:26,983 --> 00:50:28,818
Come to the picnic tomorrow, please.

718
00:50:28,901 --> 00:50:30,820
It's near the workplace
of my former workmate

719
00:50:30,903 --> 00:50:31,821
in Royal Mansour.

720
00:50:31,904 --> 00:50:34,240
I already said no, bro.
I'll just rest instead.

721
00:50:34,323 --> 00:50:36,617
What if I told you that there's
a lot of car owners there?

722
00:50:36,701 --> 00:50:39,328
If they have a car,
they'll also need a mechanic.

723
00:50:39,412 --> 00:50:42,165
I'll also bring a friend with me
so you won't get bored.

724
00:50:42,248 --> 00:50:44,083
All you think of are women.

725
00:50:44,167 --> 00:50:46,294
I've been studying the locations
of the CCTV cameras.

726
00:50:46,753 --> 00:50:48,045
Yana?

727
00:50:48,629 --> 00:50:49,547
- Yana!
- Oh?

728
00:50:49,630 --> 00:50:51,215
- Teo!
- What are you doing here?

729
00:50:51,299 --> 00:50:52,633
Are you following me?

730
00:50:52,717 --> 00:50:54,927
No, I was just delivering some pizza.

731
00:50:55,011 --> 00:50:56,679
- Ah.
- I just finished my shift.

732
00:50:56,763 --> 00:50:58,723
- Hi, I'm Jepoy.
- Meet Jepoy.

733
00:50:58,806 --> 00:51:00,516
I'm Teo's co-worker and roommate.

734
00:51:01,768 --> 00:51:03,311
I invited Teo to join our picnic tomorrow.

735
00:51:03,394 --> 00:51:04,479
You should come!

736
00:51:04,562 --> 00:51:06,355
Thanks, but I have a lot of work to do.

737
00:51:06,439 --> 00:51:08,524
- Too bad.
- What a shame.

738
00:51:08,608 --> 00:51:12,320
Teo said he has many friends
who can give you a job.

739
00:51:12,403 --> 00:51:13,738
- Yes, I know them!
- Don't you need one

740
00:51:13,821 --> 00:51:14,989
for Ms. Nadia?

741
00:51:20,077 --> 00:51:21,078
You know what?

742
00:51:21,579 --> 00:51:24,415
Filipino gatherings are not
complete without <i>pancit.</i>

743
00:51:24,499 --> 00:51:26,125
<i>- Pancit?</i>
<i>- Pancit!</i>

744
00:51:26,209 --> 00:51:27,960
You seem to be having fun, don't you?

745
00:51:28,461 --> 00:51:30,129
You don't seem to have any problems.

746
00:51:30,254 --> 00:51:32,507
First problem, homesickness.

747
00:51:32,590 --> 00:51:34,091
Second, money.

748
00:51:34,592 --> 00:51:36,636
Third, love life.

749
00:51:37,094 --> 00:51:38,888
Filipinos have a lot of burden.

750
00:51:38,971 --> 00:51:40,765
But, it's just a matter of transporting.

751
00:51:40,848 --> 00:51:42,892
I'll introduce you to
the Filipinos here in Morocco.

752
00:51:44,101 --> 00:51:45,311
N... no!

753
00:51:45,645 --> 00:51:46,938
Don't mind me.

754
00:51:47,021 --> 00:51:48,397
Just introduce me next time.

755
00:51:48,481 --> 00:51:50,066
I thought you needed a side hustle?

756
00:51:52,693 --> 00:51:54,904
Don't you really get out a lot here?

757
00:51:54,987 --> 00:51:58,699
Teo told me you were
born and raised here in Morocco.

758
00:51:59,408 --> 00:52:01,244
Don't have any Filipino friends?

759
00:52:03,996 --> 00:52:08,417
I have friends, but most of them
are Moroccans and Spaniards.

760
00:52:09,710 --> 00:52:10,920
And then...

761
00:52:11,587 --> 00:52:14,090
There's Teo.

762
00:52:14,715 --> 00:52:16,217
Teo is my friend.

763
00:52:17,677 --> 00:52:18,928
Friends!

764
00:52:19,011 --> 00:52:20,930
That's where it all starts.

765
00:52:21,013 --> 00:52:22,431
Just eat there!

766
00:52:22,515 --> 00:52:24,475
- You talk too much.
- Oh, well!

767
00:52:26,269 --> 00:52:27,520
Did you have fun?

768
00:52:27,895 --> 00:52:29,230
Mm...

769
00:52:29,313 --> 00:52:30,231
Yes.

770
00:52:30,314 --> 00:52:32,400
Good! Because we'll do this more often.

771
00:52:32,483 --> 00:52:36,195
Didn't you tell me to make
the most of our time together?

772
00:52:37,196 --> 00:52:38,281
What's that, Teo?

773
00:52:39,490 --> 00:52:40,700
Are you courting me?

774
00:52:40,783 --> 00:52:42,410
Courting? Is that still a thing?

775
00:52:43,494 --> 00:52:44,704
But seriously.

776
00:52:45,204 --> 00:52:46,414
What if I am?

777
00:52:47,206 --> 00:52:49,292
I'll court you until you say yes to me.

778
00:52:53,921 --> 00:52:54,839
Teo...

779
00:52:54,922 --> 00:52:56,632
Why are you acting like that?

780
00:52:58,551 --> 00:53:00,428
Why are you reacting so badly?

781
00:53:00,511 --> 00:53:01,637
You can just say
you don't want me to court you.

782
00:53:01,721 --> 00:53:03,222
Okay, fine. I won't make
a move on you anymore.

783
00:53:03,306 --> 00:53:04,432
Teo, wait.

784
00:53:04,515 --> 00:53:05,600
- Huh?
- I have allergies.

785
00:53:05,683 --> 00:53:07,560
I am allergic...

786
00:53:07,643 --> 00:53:08,936
I am allergic to shrimp.

787
00:53:09,020 --> 00:53:10,688
I already feel itchy.

788
00:53:10,813 --> 00:53:13,107
Why didn't you say so?
The <i>palabok</i> had shrimp in it!

789
00:53:13,190 --> 00:53:14,400
Let's hurry!

790
00:53:14,483 --> 00:53:16,027
Can you still walk?

791
00:53:18,571 --> 00:53:20,907
Just take these medicines
and you'll be okay.

792
00:53:21,407 --> 00:53:23,409
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

793
00:53:24,911 --> 00:53:26,037
Hmm.

794
00:53:26,120 --> 00:53:28,122
You really had
an allergic reaction to shrimp.

795
00:53:28,497 --> 00:53:30,875
We're lucky you were
immediately given medication.

796
00:53:30,958 --> 00:53:33,544
Well, can I get discharged now?

797
00:53:35,087 --> 00:53:37,214
You are in too much of a hurry.

798
00:53:38,841 --> 00:53:40,468
Get some rest first. You need it.

799
00:53:45,890 --> 00:53:46,724
Where are you?

800
00:53:46,807 --> 00:53:48,768
Khaled has been looking for you!

801
00:53:48,851 --> 00:53:50,102
I'm on my way home.

802
00:53:50,186 --> 00:53:51,312
Is Teo with you?

803
00:53:53,397 --> 00:53:54,231
Huh?

804
00:53:54,315 --> 00:53:55,399
So, you're really with him.

805
00:53:55,483 --> 00:53:57,234
Like I said, I'm on my way home now.

806
00:53:57,318 --> 00:53:59,403
Besides, I'm not neglecting
our work, okay?

807
00:53:59,487 --> 00:54:00,821
I know, I know.

808
00:54:00,905 --> 00:54:03,908
But if Khaled finds out,
you might be harmed.

809
00:54:04,116 --> 00:54:07,119
Why would you even
keep things secret from me?

810
00:54:07,328 --> 00:54:08,204
You are in love.

811
00:54:09,622 --> 00:54:10,873
You're acting like that can happen.

812
00:54:10,957 --> 00:54:13,417
But you know the difference
between what's forbidden

813
00:54:13,501 --> 00:54:14,919
and what you really feel.

814
00:54:15,002 --> 00:54:17,797
<i>The truth is, you already like him.</i>

815
00:54:18,089 --> 00:54:19,924
<i>That's one step away from loving him.</i>

816
00:54:20,091 --> 00:54:21,300
No.

817
00:54:21,592 --> 00:54:22,885
That can't happen.

818
00:54:22,969 --> 00:54:24,679
<i>We have so many problems.</i>

819
00:54:25,888 --> 00:54:27,390
There's a lot of obstacles.

820
00:54:29,517 --> 00:54:31,227
Teo will just be in danger.

821
00:54:32,687 --> 00:54:34,146
That's unfair to him.

822
00:54:38,901 --> 00:54:41,237
Okay, bye. I'll call you later.

823
00:54:41,320 --> 00:54:43,406
Sorry, it took too long. Here it is.

824
00:54:44,365 --> 00:54:45,908
- Be careful, it's hot.
- What is that?

825
00:54:45,992 --> 00:54:47,076
Coffee!

826
00:54:47,159 --> 00:54:49,328
- Didn't you say you wanted one?
- Thank you.

827
00:54:49,412 --> 00:54:51,372
Let's get going.

828
00:54:55,960 --> 00:54:57,628
I was in Jardin de Soleil.

829
00:55:00,047 --> 00:55:02,550
There's a ton of CCTV cameras
even outside its premises.

830
00:55:03,801 --> 00:55:05,011
Diane...

831
00:55:05,511 --> 00:55:07,013
How long will Sheikh Jamal be there?

832
00:55:07,096 --> 00:55:08,472
Until Monday.

833
00:55:10,850 --> 00:55:12,184
Just in time.

834
00:55:15,521 --> 00:55:17,523
That's my mother's schedule
for her chemotherapy.

835
00:55:18,315 --> 00:55:20,609
After this mission...

836
00:55:21,318 --> 00:55:23,112
we'll finally be able to escape.

837
00:55:25,489 --> 00:55:26,866
Escape?

838
00:55:27,283 --> 00:55:28,492
We'll run away, Yana?

839
00:55:30,703 --> 00:55:32,121
What do you think, Gimo?

840
00:55:32,204 --> 00:55:34,957
With how big this operation is
and how much we'll be earning,

841
00:55:35,041 --> 00:55:37,626
will I just let Khaled take it all?

842
00:55:38,044 --> 00:55:40,296
I like that plan, Yana.

843
00:55:41,714 --> 00:55:42,923
But are you sure?

844
00:55:43,007 --> 00:55:44,925
Are you sure you can take Khaled on?

845
00:55:46,093 --> 00:55:47,803
Because I really want
to escape this already.

846
00:55:47,928 --> 00:55:49,805
Look at what he did to me, Boss Yana.

847
00:55:52,141 --> 00:55:54,351
Yes, Gimo. This is it!

848
00:55:57,521 --> 00:55:59,023
Not yet.

849
00:56:01,108 --> 00:56:02,943
Can I take revenge on him, Yana?

850
00:56:03,027 --> 00:56:04,987
I'll just give him a kick!

851
00:56:12,661 --> 00:56:14,413
Goodbye, Khaled.

852
00:56:33,015 --> 00:56:35,017
<i>♪ It's not easy ♪</i>

853
00:56:36,519 --> 00:56:39,021
<i>♪ To navigate this world ♪</i>

854
00:56:41,565 --> 00:56:43,484
<i>The sheikh gave me this.</i>

855
00:56:44,485 --> 00:56:47,029
<i>He said it's Moroccan amethyst.</i>

856
00:56:47,113 --> 00:56:49,323
<i>Symbol of honor...</i>

857
00:56:50,366 --> 00:56:51,492
<i>truth...</i>

858
00:56:52,493 --> 00:56:53,994
<i>and love.</i>

859
00:56:55,788 --> 00:57:01,794
<i>♪ But destiny kept us apart ♪</i>

860
00:57:04,630 --> 00:57:11,387
<i>♪ I loved you not because I need you ♪</i>

861
00:57:12,012 --> 00:57:16,267
<i>♪ I needed you because ♪</i>

862
00:57:16,350 --> 00:57:21,397
<i>♪ I love you ♪</i>

863
00:57:22,022 --> 00:57:24,984
<i>♪ It will not be gone ♪</i>

864
00:57:26,026 --> 00:57:28,487
<i>♪ It will not be gone ♪</i>

865
00:57:29,405 --> 00:57:33,325
<i>♪ Even if I'm left alone ♪</i>

866
00:57:33,409 --> 00:57:35,578
<i>♪ Nothing will fade away ♪</i>

867
00:57:35,661 --> 00:57:38,622
<i>♪ Nothing will change ♪</i>

868
00:57:38,706 --> 00:57:42,835
<i>♪ There will be no regrets ♪</i>

869
00:57:42,918 --> 00:57:45,838
<i>♪ In everything I gave ♪</i>

870
00:57:45,921 --> 00:57:50,509
<i>♪ You gave me life ♪</i>

871
00:57:50,593 --> 00:57:57,433
<i>♪ And oxygen that I breathe ♪</i>

872
00:58:00,060 --> 00:58:03,189
<i>♪ I can't afford to lose you ♪</i>

873
00:58:12,698 --> 00:58:15,576
<i>♪ A story was made ♪</i>

874
00:58:16,702 --> 00:58:22,917
<i>♪ We loved and hurt each other you and I ♪</i>

875
00:58:24,210 --> 00:58:30,591
<i>♪ But we just proved even more ♪</i>

876
00:58:32,760 --> 00:58:38,182
<i>♪ How deep our love is ♪</i>

877
00:58:50,194 --> 00:58:53,405
<i>♪ Nothing will fade away ♪</i>

878
00:58:54,114 --> 00:58:57,201
<i>♪ It will not be gone ♪</i>

879
00:58:57,284 --> 00:58:58,410
Yana?

880
00:58:58,494 --> 00:59:01,413
<i>♪ Even if I'm left alone ♪</i>

881
00:59:01,497 --> 00:59:04,291
<i>♪ Nothing will fade away ♪</i>

882
00:59:04,375 --> 00:59:07,211
<i>♪ Nothing will change ♪</i>

883
00:59:07,294 --> 00:59:11,215
<i>♪ There will be no regrets ♪</i>

884
00:59:11,298 --> 00:59:14,009
<i>♪ In everything I gave ♪</i>

885
00:59:14,093 --> 00:59:19,014
<i>♪ You gave me life ♪</i>

886
00:59:19,098 --> 00:59:25,729
<i>♪ And oxygen that I breathe ♪</i>

887
00:59:28,983 --> 00:59:31,819
<i>♪ I can't afford to lose you ♪</i>

888
00:59:41,078 --> 00:59:43,205
<i>Is Yana here?</i>
<i>She's your delivery rider.</i>

889
00:59:43,289 --> 00:59:44,915
<i>She doesn't work here.</i>

890
00:59:44,999 --> 00:59:46,625
<i>Ace, she's here.</i>

891
00:59:47,376 --> 00:59:48,752
<i>I thought you were</i>
<i>just a pickpocket,</i>

892
00:59:48,836 --> 00:59:50,421
<i>- but you're a serious criminal!</i>
- <i>You don't know anything.</i>

893
00:59:50,504 --> 00:59:52,548
<i>I really don't! You deceived me!</i>
<i>You made a fool out of me!</i>

894
00:59:52,631 --> 00:59:54,591
<i>- What are you, a fake person?</i>
- Yes! To others!

895
00:59:55,509 --> 00:59:57,469
<i>You can't get away</i>
<i>with everything you've done.</i>

896
00:59:57,553 --> 00:59:59,888
- Give up!
- Chameleon!

897
01:00:08,022 --> 01:00:09,940
Yana!
